C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20recent%20exercise%2C%20part%20of%20efforts%20to%20learn%20from%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20examined%20how%20NATO%20allies%20ought%20to%20plan%20and%20prepare%20for%20the%20threat%20posed%20by%20uncrewed%20surface%20vessels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine's%20defense%20ministry%20said%20Friday%20that%20its%20team%20defeated%20NATO%20forces%20in%20a%20military%20exercise%20off%20the%20coast%20of%20Portugal.%20Across%20five%20scenarios%2C%20a%20Ukraine-led%20%26quot%3Bred%26quot%3B%20team%20%E2%80%94%20which%20also%20included%20US%2C%20British%2C%20Spanish%2C%20and%20other%20units%20%E2%80%94%20beat%20the%20%26quot%3Bblue%26quot%3B%20team%20made%20up%20of%20NATO%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20all%20five%20scenarios%2C%20Ukrainians%20struck%20the%20ports%20and%20convoys%20of%20the%20simulated%20adversary%2C%26quot%3B%20Ukraine%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20red%20aggressor%20team%20used%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-naval-drones-scaring-away-russian-helicopters-commander-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMagura%20V7%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20class%20of%20USVs%20developed%20by%20Kyiv%20and%20capable%20of%20fulfilling%20intelligence%2C%20surveillance%2C%20and%20reconnaissance%20roles%2C%20as%20well%20as%20combat%20and%20mine%20countermeasure%20duties.%20In%20one%20scenario%2C%20the%20red%20team%20used%20the%20drones%20to%20simulate%20the%20targeting%20and%20sinking%20of%20a%20NATO%20frigate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20said%20a%20NATO%20spokesperson%20acknowledged%20the%20threat%20of%20naval%20drones%20had%20been%20previously%20underestimated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225249%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22tk%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69bd6b1175bee4e0ee55e72c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223499%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3Etk%3Cp%3EGlobal%20Images%20Ukraine%2FGlobal%20Images%20Ukraine%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20annual%20REPMUS%2FDynamic%20Messenger%20exercises%20are%20part%20of%20NATO's%20Operational%20Experimentation%20series%20in%20which%20allies%20test%20and%20evaluate%20new%20maritime%20capabilities.%20Last%20fall's%20Robotic%20Experimentation%20and%20Prototyping%20using%20Maritime%20Uncrewed%20Systems%20(REPMUS)%20drill%20included%20two%20dozen%20allied%20navies%20and%20also%20tested%20Ukraine's%20naval%20drones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENATO%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release%20that%20these%20tests%20allowed%20the%20alliance%20to%20learn%20lessons%20on%20the%20use%20of%20drones%20from%20Ukraine%2C%20including%20how%20NATO%20navies%20can%20integrate%20drones%20into%20their%20naval%20forces%20as%20well%20as%20defend%20from%20enemy%20uncrewed%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20REPMUS%2FDynamic%20Messenger%20exercises%20also%20aim%20to%20simulate%20realistic%20combat%20conditions%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-war-with-iran-shows-unseen-battle-vital-modern-war-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eelectronic%20warfare%20interference%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20jamming%2C%20and%20other%20drone%20countermeasures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkraine%20lacks%20the%20ships%20necessary%20for%20traditional%20naval%20combat%20power%2C%20so%20it%20has%2C%20instead%2C%20relied%20heavily%20on%20missiles%20and%20naval%20drones%20to%20confront%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-emptied-warships-from-black-sea-fleet-base-returned-them-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ERussia's%20Black%20Sea%20Fleet%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20drones%20have%20damaged%20or%20destroyed%20dozens%20of%20Russian%20warships%20and%20vessels%20throughout%20the%20war.%20Kyiv%20has%20also%20used%20its%20naval%20drones%20to%20target%20infrastructure%2C%20such%20as%20ports%2C%20bridges%2C%20and%20offshore%20oil%20platforms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKyiv%20continues%20to%20invest%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-re